Vice President Joe Biden is set to make a Recovery Act announcement on Earth Day at the New Carrollton WMATA Station. He will be joined by United States Senator Ben Cardin and Maryland Governor Martin O'Malley. The event will take place at 9:30 AM EDT in Landover, MD. The press entrance and parking details are provided in the advisory. Media outlets must RSVP with their information by 5:00 PM on April 21st. The ground contact person is Karen Burchard at 703-786-2369.